9. Saccharomyces cerevisiae genomic extraction
Mix the bacterial fluid into the 2ml centrifuge tube and collect the cells by centrifugation at 12000rpm 2min;
Add 1ml sterile water or washing buffer and wash 1 time;
Adding equal volume glass beads, and adding 100μL TENTS, using a cell crusher to break cells for 1min;
Add 600 L TENTS, mix upside down, then put in room temperature for 1min;
Centrifuge 8000 rpm, 1 min, pipette extract supernatant, transfer to the new 2ml EP tube;
Add the volume of phenol: chloroform (1:1) [pay attention to exact the lower layer], mixing evenly, place in room temperature10 min;
Centrifuged 10 min 120000 rpm, carefully remove the supernatant with a 200 L pipette [pay attention to not to the middle of the protein layer];
Add 2-3 times the volume of anhydrous ethanol, 1/10 volume of NaAc, mixing evenly, ice bath for 40 min-1h;
Centrifuged 10 min 12000 rpm and discard supernatant;
Add 1 ml 75% ethanol, mix evenly [wash precipitation], centrifuge 5 min 12000 rpm;
Discard the supernatant [caution not to drop the bottom white], Short, the residue is removed with a pipette, and the 37 degrees incubator is dried

